Different anon (this one >>38094806) checking in.

Would you like to engage in some interactive world-building? You get to make all decisions on what you're comfortable with, but we can kick ideas & suggestions around /hmofa/ and develop some Rules for your world. For future reference, folks could then drop a greentext in that setting or (maybe some day) go for a story. Perhaps even complimented by your art.

You had said you only wanted wolves in your world previously. But, you've now drawn foxes and raccoons.

I suggest that you go with this as a framework, that you want fairly minimal species in this world. Perhaps you can go with various canids, which would give you wolves, vulpines, painted dogs, a couple other close relations. Subspecies of those give you probably about 20 or even up to 30 races/species to work with. Something to develop over time, not necessarily in one week.

Add to that raccoons, which are (distant) mustelids, pretty much their own branch. So you'd have a couple subspecies, plus tanuki from Japan/Asia, and an odd relative of theirs is the red panda. You could skip on the rest (weasels, otters, etc.) or maybe include wolverines & badgers. Eventually.

If you go this route, no need to have any other species of anthros, and you've got a collection here with a fair diversity to cover various countries and regions.

Next question: what's the tech level of your world?
